_filter_names()
---------------

Set up
	>>> makepath('trace.log').write_text('hello')
	>>> files_in_directory_under_test = l.get_files([directory_under_test])
	>>> show(files_in_directory_under_test)
	>>> names_of_files_in_directory_under_test = l.get_names(files_in_directory_under_test)
	>>> show(names_of_files_in_directory_under_test)

The _filter_names() method removes all names
	which do not have at least one wanted file
	A file's extension decides whether it is wanted
	For example, the ly module does not want log files

	>>> 'ly' in names_of_files_in_directory_under_test, 'trace' in names_of_files_in_directory_under_test
	(True, True)
	>>> ly._filter_names(names_of_files_in_directory_under_test)
	>>> 'ly' in names_of_files_in_directory_under_test, 'trace' in names_of_files_in_directory_under_test
	(True, False)

Tear down
	>>> makepath('trace.log').remove()
